{"questionId":"3497358","questionHtml":"<p>Deduce the scattering angle for the photon.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(for this interaction)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Δ</mtext><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>e</mtext></msub><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>e</mtext></msub><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and therefore&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;must equal 1&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>so cos theta = 0 and theta = 90 deg&nbsp;✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3497358","referenceCode":"EXE.2.HL.TZ0.20biii","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Deduce the scattering angle for the photon.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E.2 Quantum physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}